<inglise> The Commission shall inform the Member States of those applications before it takes a decision, taking into account respect for confidentiality. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon teatab enne otsuse tegemist nendest taotlustest liikmesriikidele, v&otilde;ttes arvesse konfidentsiaalsuskohustust. </eesti>
<inglise> This decision shall be published in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> Otsus avaldatakse Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The transitional regime shall be of limited duration and shall be linked to expiry of the commitments or guarantees referred to in paragraph 1. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekukorra kehtimise aeg on piiratud ning seotud l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kohustuste v&otilde;i garantiide t&auml;htajaga. </eesti>
<inglise> The transitional regime may cover derogations from Chapter IV, VI and VII of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekukord v&otilde;ib h&otilde;lmata erandeid k&auml;esoleva direktiivi IV, VI ja VII peat&uuml;kist. </eesti>
<inglise> Applications for a transitional regime must be notified to the Commission no later than one year after the entry into force of this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekukorra taotlustest tuleb komisjonile teatada hiljemalt &uuml;ks aasta p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States which can demonstrate, after the Directive has been brought into force, that there are substantial problems for the operation of their small isolated systems, may apply for derogations from the relevant provisions of Chapter IV, V, VI, VII, which may be granted to them by the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid, kes p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&otilde;ustamist suudavad t&otilde;endada, et nende v&auml;ikeste isoleeritud v&otilde;rkude t&ouml;&ouml;s on olulisi probleeme, v&otilde;ivad taotleda erandeid IV, V, VI ja VII peat&uuml;ki vastavatest s&auml;tetest ja komisjon v&otilde;ib need erandid neile anda. </eesti>
<inglise> The latter shall inform the Member States of those applications prior to taking a decision, taking into account respect for confidentiality. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon teatab enne otsuse tegemist nendest taotlustest liikmesriikidele, v&otilde;ttes arvesse konfidentsiaalsuskohustust. </eesti>
